      "writtenOn": "2020-09-02T01:49:51Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Just in general I strongly recommend you implement the actual logic in a separate function that doesn\u0027t depend on router.Context, and just takes a regular context.Context, parsed arguments, maybe a http.ResponseWriter and returns an error. That way the code of the handler is less convoluted (ctx everywhere instead of c.Context), and it can be tested in isolation from HTTP-level stuff.\n\n\nSomething like:\n\n  func treeHandler(c *router.Context) {\n    err :\u003d renderTree(c.Context, fullInstanceName(c.Params), c.Writer)\n    if err !\u003d nil {\n       ...\n    }\n  }\n\n  func renderTree(ctx context.Context, instance string, rw http.ResponseWriter) error {\n     ...\n  }",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 50,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 61,
        "endChar": 1
      },
      "revId": "9c0d03a1a993bfc1fa3f0cbb638ef87891861a22",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
