      "message": "as *unit* tests go, this is not a very good unit test since it sets up a lot of server stuff.\n\nIf you want to test a middleware specifically, this is fine. But for testing individual handlers a much simpler approach is to test them individually without all this cruft:\n\n  ctx :\u003d context.Background()\n  ctx \u003d auth.WithState(ctx, \u0026authtest.FakeState{\n    Identity: \"user:user@example.com\",\n  })\n  \n  rr :\u003d httptest.NewRecorder()\n  err :\u003d renderTree(ctx, \"instance\", rr)\n  ...",
